output.title: Build Passed
output.summary: The build **passed**, just like the previous build.
output.text:
This is a normal build for the master branch. You should be able to reproduce it by checking out the branch locally. ## Jobs and Stages This build has **four jobs**, running in parallel.
Job Go ENV State
14058.1 1.12.1 \["SHARD=0"\] passed
14058.2 1.12.1 \["SHARD=1"\] passed
14058.3 1.12.1 \["SHARD=2"\] passed
14058.4 1.12.1 \["SHARD=3"\] passed
## Build Configuration Build Option | Setting -----------------|-------------- Language | Go Operating System | Linux (Trusty) Go Version | 1.12.1
Build Configuration 
{
  "go": [
    "1.12.1"
  ],
  "os": "linux",
  "env": [
    "SHARD=0",
    "SHARD=1",
    "SHARD=2",
    "SHARD=3"
  ],
  "dist": "trusty",
  "cache": {
    "directories": [
      "$HOME/.gocache"
    ]
  },
  "group": "stable",
  "script": [
    "docker version",
    "echo \"TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST $TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST_BRANCH $TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST_BRANCH TRAVIS_COMMIT_RANGE $TRAVIS_COMMIT_RANGE\"",
    "if [[ \"$TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST\" != \"false\" && \"$TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST_SHA\" != \"\" ]] ; then base_version=$(git merge-base master ${TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST_SHA}) ; export AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE=\"${base_version}..${TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST_SHA}\" ; elif [[ \"$TRAVIS_COMMIT_RANGE\" != \"\" ]] ; then export AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE=\"${TRAVIS_COMMIT_RANGE}\" ; else export AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE=\"master\" ; fi",
    "if [[ \"$AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE\" != \"master\" ]] && git log --pretty=format:'%s %b' $AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE | grep '\\[build all\\]' > /dev/null ; then export AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE=\"master\" ; fi",
    "ci/make_shard.sh ${SHARD} ${NUM_SHARDS} \"${AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE}\" test ;",
    "if [[ \"$TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST\" == \"false\" && \"$TRAVIS_BRANCH\" == \"master\" ]] ; then ci/make_shard.sh ${SHARD} ${NUM_SHARDS} \"${AFFECTED_COMMIT_RANGE}\" push_image ; fi"
  ],
  ".result": "configured",
  "install": [
    "go get github.com/Wattpad/affected"
  ],
  "branches": {
    "only": [
      "master",
      "/feature/"
    ]
  },
  "language": "go",
  "services": [
    "docker",
    "mysql"
  ],
  "notifications": {
    "slack": {
      "secure": ""
    }
  },
  "before_install": [
    "export PATH=${PATH}:${TRAVIS_BUILD_DIR}/vendor/bin",
    "export GOPATH=\"${TRAVIS_BUILD_DIR}/vendor:${TRAVIS_BUILD_DIR}/wattpad\"",
    "pip install --user awscli",
    "export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/.local/bin",
    "$(aws ecr get-login --no-include-email --region us-east-1)",
    "export NUM_SHARDS=4"
  ]
}

app.name: Travis CI
app.description:
Test and deploy with confidence. Trusted by over 800,000 users, Travis CI is the leading hosted continuous integration system.

Supporting over 30 different languages, including Ruby, Mac/iOS, and Docker, Travis CI is built for everyone.

Free for open source, and with a 100 build trial for private projects, getting setup takes just 2 minutes.
